{
    "id": "astronomy/basic-telescope",
    "title": "Assemble a Simple Telescope",
    "description": "Use 50 mm and 20 mm magnifying lenses, masking tape, a cardboard mailing tube and a camera tripod to build a simple refractor for viewing Jupiter's moons. Work in the shade and never aim at the Sun.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/simple_cardboard_telescope_assembly.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/nova.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Nova here. Gather a 50 mm lens, 20 mm lens, mailing tube, masking tape, and a camera tripod. Inspect for chips, work in shade, wear eye protection, and keep the tube away from the Sun. Ready?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "choose-build",
                    "text": "I'm ready.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "0254a829-9002-4a75-8af2-03cd961601da",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "7aafe032-86e2-449e-8e25-8148f8c58c17",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "2794503d-fbe7-4031-a63e-deac531f9784",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "49fb255e-a4c3-48e4-bca7-4c3781fdb98b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "13aaff4f-e4ba-4e4a-b21b-5852b118a0ed",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "choose-build",
            "text": "Pick a build path: objective-first for precise centering, or dry-fit first if your tube fit is tight. Both paths still require a stability check before sky use.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build-objective-first",
                    "text": "Objective-first assembly"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "build-dry-fit",
                    "text": "Dry-fit then tape"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "build-objective-first",
            "text": "Tape the 50 mm objective lens to the front first, then seat the 20 mm eyepiece. Keep lens edges pointed away from your face while adjusting tape tension.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-basic-telescope",
                    "text": "Objective-first assembly complete."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Move to stability verification.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "build-dry-fit",
            "text": "Dry-fit both lenses to check spacing, then tape the objective and eyepiece after alignment marks are set. Re-cap lenses between adjustments to avoid scratches.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "assemble-basic-telescope",
                    "text": "Dry-fit path complete."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Move to stability verification.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify",
            "text": "Mount the tube on the tripod and check wobble. If the image jitters or the tube slips, stop and re-tape before observing. Never test toward the Sun.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Stable image confirmed on a distant ground target.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "f439b57a-9df3-4bd9-9b6e-042476ceecf5",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "recover",
                    "text": "I found lens blur or wobble during setup."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "recover",
            "text": "Good catch. Re-seat loose tape, shorten the tube overlap if slipping, and retighten tripod joints before retrying. If glass is chipped, pause and replace that lens.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "choose-build",
                    "text": "Rebuild and re-verify."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Excellent craftsmanship. Regular stargazing sharpens navigation. Cap both lenses before storing and keep the telescope away from heat and direct sunlight.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Thanks, Nova."
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
